Workflow
File scanning: The app walks through the specified folder (SCAN_FOLDER) and collects all file names.

Categorization: Each file is matched against known extensions (e.g., .jpg, .pdf, .mp3). If no match is found, it is placed in the ‚ÄúOthers‚Äù category.

Counting: The number of files in each category is calculated.

Template rendering: Clean lists of categories and counts are passed to the Jinja2 template.

Visualization: Chart.js renders a pie chart showing the distribution of files.

Usage
Update the SCAN_FOLDER variable in app.py to the folder you want to analyze.

Run the application:

bash
python app.py
Open your browser at http://127.0.0.1:5000/.

View the pie chart showing file distribution.

Customization
Change folder: Modify SCAN_FOLDER in app.py to scan a different directory.

Add file types: Extend the FILE_TYPES dictionary to include more categories.

Adjust chart size: In dashboard.html, set <canvas id="pieChart" width="400" height="400"> or use CSS to control chart dimensions.

Limitations
Only scans one folder at a time.

Does not display actual file names, only counts.

Large folders may take longer to process.

Future Enhancements
Add drill-down functionality to show actual file names when clicking on a pie slice.

Allow users to select folders dynamically via the web interface.

Integrate file size analysis to show storage usage per category.

Add multiple chart types (bar chart, doughnut chart) for comparison.
